es\nBeery and Delilah Beery of .New\nLondon, departed Thursday for Ohio,\nwhere a reunion of the Beery family\nwill be held.\nMrs. Rachel Kellum and daughter\nAlma, were guests at the William\nTrueblood home, at Denova, last week.\nMr. and Mrs. C. Scott spent Thurs\nday at Keokuk, where medical aid\nwas sought for the latter.\ni!\nDM\nUPON\nmakes money gro\u00bbjf quickly\u2014is yours\ngrowing this way? A deposit of $1 a\nwoeli for twenty years will amount to,\n$1,417.22.\nWhy not have your money 0*\nwork for you?\nThe State Certral\nSavings Bank\nCapital $100,000.00. Surplus $200,000.00\nto Keokuk, after several weeks 8Pen*\nwith relatives here.\nMr. and Mrs. T. M. Johnson AND\nson Harry of Iowa City, Mr. and J,r8'\nCharles Johnson of Green Castle,\nHorace Lester of Washington state,\nMr. and Mrs. Ed Bell and two chil\ndren of Leon, were called to Saleffl\nlast week by the serious Illness and\ndeath of their mother, Mrs. Harriet\nLester.\nJudge Wlthrow of Mt. Pleasant,\nvisited his cousin, Mrs. Sadie A*\nmond, Saturday.\nMiss Florence Bicksler is hom\u00ab\nfrom Chicago, wh^re she attende\nschool.\nJudge Withrow, Mr. and Mrs. G\u00ae0,\nCramer of Mt. Pleasant, Wesley\nRunion and wiie, Mr. and\nMrs.\nGeorge\nAltpn, Mr. and Mrs. D. C. Johnson.\nRobert Johnson and sistci's, Corde a\nand Mattie, of Hitlsboro, and a large\nnumber from Mt. Hamill attended\nfuneral of their friend, Mrs. Harr\nLester, Saturday afternoon.\nMr. and Mrs. Charles Johnson le\nfor their home at Green Castle,\nMonday morning.\nE. E. Bell and family expect to r\u00bb\nturn to Leon Wednesday.","height":"27036","width":"20855"}}
